\newlabel{fig:kantorovich-permutation-versus-splitting}{{3.3}{26}{From permutation matrices to splitting couplings. When the two empirical measures have the same number of atoms and uniform weights, an optimal plan can be a permutation matrix. Once target masses are nonuniform, the admissible set $\CouplingsD (\a ,\b )$ also contains plans in which one source sends mass to several targets and several sources merge into the same target}{figure.3.3}{}}
