\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.1}{\ignorespaces Discrete Kantorovich dual potentials for the quadratic cost $C_{i,j}=|x_i-y_j|^2$. In each panel the upper strip shows the fixed source histogram in red and the target histogram in blue: a balanced bimodal target, a more strongly shifted target, and a three-component mixture. The lower strip shows an optimal pair of dual vectors $(\mathrm  {f},\mathrm  {g})$, with gauge chosen so that $\langle \mathrm  {f},\,\mathrm  {a}\rangle =0$. Complementary slackness states that mass can be transported only through entries where $\mathrm  {f}_i+\mathrm  {g}_j=C_{i,j}$.}}{45}{figure.4.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:dual-kantorovich-discrete-potentials}{{4.1}{45}{Discrete Kantorovich dual potentials for the quadratic cost $C_{i,j}=|x_i-y_j|^2$. In each panel the upper strip shows the fixed source histogram in red and the target histogram in blue: a balanced bimodal target, a more strongly shifted target, and a three-component mixture. The lower strip shows an optimal pair of dual vectors $(\fD ,\gD )$, with gauge chosen so that $\dotp {\fD }{\a }=0$. Complementary slackness states that mass can be transported only through entries where $\fD _i+\gD _j=C_{i,j}$}{figure.4.1}{}}
