\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {9.6}{\ignorespaces Trace and spectral gauges for displacement covariances. The trace gauge minimizes the average squared displacement and gives the usual quadratic transport plan from a two-disk source silhouette to a heart-shaped target. The $\lambda _{\qopname  \relax m{max}}$ gauge penalizes the worst projected displacement variance; the displayed plan is obtained by approximating the robust formulation with a small finite set of directions. The last two rows render the corresponding displacement interpolations as kernel-smoothed density images, with the same convention as Figure\nobreakspace  {}\ref  {fig:monge-shape-mccann-interpolation}: white means zero density, and high density saturates in the red-to-blue interpolation color of the corresponding time. The figure is illustrative: it visualizes how changing the gauge changes the coupling and the induced interpolation geometry.}}{111}{figure.9.6}\protected@file@percent }
